 by causing dopamine and serotonin suppression - and by being\nsuppressed by them, the adversity processing circuit competes with reward\nprocessing circuit for control of choice behaviour and affective states. We\npropose stimulating effect of dopamine and calming inhibitory effect of\nserotonin on the active avoidance circuit involving amygdala, linked to threat\nprocessing, anger, fear, self-defense and violences. We describe causes and\nroles of dopamine and serotonin signaling, and mental dysfunctions. We add new\nidea on vACC role in signaling that we are doing well and in inducing\nserotonin, when we gain/reach safety, comfort, valuable resources,\nsocial/biological rewards, affection or goals.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Apr 2013 19:05:50 GMT"},{"version":"v10","created":"Wed, 14 May 2014 14:54:51 GMT"},{"version":"v11","created":"Tue, 9 Sep 2014 10:10:38 GMT"},{"version":"v12","created":"Thu, 16 Oct 2014 08:18:23 GMT"},{"version":"v13","created":"Mon, 27 Oct 2014 15:03:28 GMT"},{"version":"v14","created":"Fri, 31 Oct 2014 17:29:02 GMT"},{"version":"v15","created":"Sat, 15 Nov 2014 12:52:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 May 2013 19:30:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 26 Jun 2013 07:23:15 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2013 12:10:03 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 22 Jan 2014 15:13:33 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 6 Feb 2014 08:09:15 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Fri, 7 Feb 2014 09:10:46 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Wed, 12 Feb 2014 10:39:41 GMT"},{"version":"v9","created":"Fri, 28 Feb 2014 18:04:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-18"}
