 fractional precisions of 2.3-5 parts in $10^9$. By comparing\nthe results with three-body quantum electrodynamics calculations, we derived an\nantiproton-to-electron mass ratio of 1,836.1526736(23), where the parenthetical\nerror represents one standard deviation. This agrees with the\nproton-to-electron value known to a similar precision.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Apr 2013 05:20:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Jun 2013 06:25:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-06-07"}
